35class QSortFilterProxyModelLessThan
36{
37public:
38 inline QSortFilterProxyModelLessThan(int column, const QModelIndex &parent,
39 const QAbstractItemModel *source,
40 const QSortFilterProxyModel *proxy)
41 : sort_column(column), source_parent(parent), source_model(source), proxy_model(proxy) {}
42
43 inline bool operator()(int r1, int r2) const
44 {
45 QModelIndex i1 = source_model->index(row: r1, column: sort_column, parent: source_parent);
46 QModelIndex i2 = source_model->index(row: r2, column: sort_column, parent: source_parent);
47 return proxy_model->lessThan(source_left: i1, source_right: i2);
48 }
49
50private:
51 int sort_column;
52 QModelIndex source_parent;
53 const QAbstractItemModel *source_model;
54 const QSortFilterProxyModel *proxy_model;
55};

81//this struct is used to store what are the rows that are removed
82//between a call to rowsAboutToBeRemoved and rowsRemoved
83//it avoids readding rows to the mapping that are currently being removed
84struct QRowsRemoval
85{
86 QRowsRemoval(const QModelIndex &parent_source, int start, int end) : parent_source(parent_source), start(start), end(end)
87 {
88 }
89
90 QRowsRemoval() : start(-1), end(-1)
91 {
92 }
93
94 bool contains(QModelIndex parent, int row) const
95 {
96 do {
97 if (parent == parent_source)
98 return row >= start && row <= end;
99 row = parent.row();
100 parent = parent.parent();
101 } while (row >= 0);
102 return false;
103 }
104private:
105 QModelIndex parent_source;
106 int start;
107 int end;
108};

256 {
257 QRegularExpression re = filter_regularexpression.value();
258 const auto cs = re.patternOptions() & QRegularExpression::CaseInsensitiveOption;
259 re.setPattern(pattern);
260 re.setPatternOptions(cs);
261 // This is a helper function, which is supposed to be called from a
262 // more complicated context. Because of that, the caller is responsible
263 // for calling notify() and removeBindingUnlessInWrapper(), if needed.
264 filter_regularexpression.setValueBypassingBindings(re);
265 }

267 inline QHash<QModelIndex, Mapping *>::const_iterator index_to_iterator(
268 const QModelIndex &proxy_index) const
269 {
270 Q_ASSERT(proxy_index.isValid());
271 Q_ASSERT(proxy_index.model() == q_func());
272 const void *p = proxy_index.internalPointer();
273 Q_ASSERT(p);
274 QHash<QModelIndex, Mapping *>::const_iterator it =
275 source_index_mapping.constFind(key: static_cast<const Mapping*>(p)->source_parent);
276 Q_ASSERT(it != source_index_mapping.constEnd());
277 Q_ASSERT(it.value());
278 return it;
279 }

398bool QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::filterAcceptsRowInternal(int source_row, const QModelIndex &source_parent) const
399{
400 Q_Q(const QSortFilterProxyModel);
401
402 if (q->filterAcceptsRow(source_row, source_parent))
403 return true;
404
405 // Go up the tree and accept this row if a parent is accepted
406 if (accept_children && recursiveParentAcceptsRow(source_parent))
407 return true;
408
409 // Go down the tree and accept this row if a child is accepted
410 if (filter_recursive && recursiveChildAcceptsRow(source_row, source_parent))
411 return true;
412
413 return false;
414}
415
416bool QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::recursiveParentAcceptsRow(const QModelIndex &source_parent) const
417{
418 Q_Q(const QSortFilterProxyModel);
419
420 if (source_parent.isValid()) {
421 const QModelIndex index = source_parent.parent();
422
423 if (q->filterAcceptsRow(source_row: source_parent.row(), source_parent: index))
424 return true;
425
426 return recursiveParentAcceptsRow(source_parent: index);
427 }
428
429 return false;
430}
431
432bool QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::recursiveChildAcceptsRow(int source_row, const QModelIndex &source_parent) const
433{
434 Q_Q(const QSortFilterProxyModel);
435
436 const QModelIndex index = model->index(row: source_row, column: 0, parent: source_parent);
437 const int count = model->rowCount(parent: index);
438
439 for (int i = 0; i < count; ++i) {
440 if (q->filterAcceptsRow(source_row: i, source_parent: index))
441 return true;
442
443 if (recursiveChildAcceptsRow(source_row: i, source_parent: index))
444 return true;
445 }
446
447 return false;
448}

450void QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::remove_from_mapping(const QModelIndex &source_parent)
451{
452 if (Mapping *m = source_index_mapping.take(key: source_parent)) {
453 for (const QModelIndex &mappedIdx : std::as_const(t&: m->mapped_children))
454 remove_from_mapping(source_parent: mappedIdx);
455 delete m;
456 }
457}

472
473IndexMap::const_iterator QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::create_mapping(
474 const QModelIndex &source_parent) const
475{
476 Q_Q(const QSortFilterProxyModel);
477
478 IndexMap::const_iterator it = source_index_mapping.constFind(key: source_parent);
479 if (it != source_index_mapping.constEnd()) // was mapped already
480 return it;
481
482 Mapping *m = new Mapping;
483
484 int source_rows = model->rowCount(parent: source_parent);
485 m->source_rows.reserve(size: source_rows);
486 for (int i = 0; i < source_rows; ++i) {
487 if (filterAcceptsRowInternal(source_row: i, source_parent))
488 m->source_rows.append(t: i);
489 }
490 int source_cols = model->columnCount(parent: source_parent);
491 m->source_columns.reserve(size: source_cols);
492 for (int i = 0; i < source_cols; ++i) {
493 if (q->filterAcceptsColumn(source_column: i, source_parent))
494 m->source_columns.append(t: i);
495 }
496
497 sort_source_rows(source_rows&: m->source_rows, source_parent);
498 m->proxy_rows.resize(size: source_rows);
499 build_source_to_proxy_mapping(proxy_to_source: m->source_rows, source_to_proxy&: m->proxy_rows);
500 m->proxy_columns.resize(size: source_cols);
501 build_source_to_proxy_mapping(proxy_to_source: m->source_columns, source_to_proxy&: m->proxy_columns);
502
503 m->source_parent = source_parent;
504
505 if (source_parent.isValid()) {
506 QModelIndex source_grand_parent = source_parent.parent();
507 IndexMap::const_iterator it2 = create_mapping(source_parent: source_grand_parent);
508 Q_ASSERT(it2 != source_index_mapping.constEnd());
509 it2.value()->mapped_children.append(t: source_parent);
510 }
511
512 it = IndexMap::const_iterator(source_index_mapping.insert(key: source_parent, value: m));
513 Q_ASSERT(it != source_index_mapping.constEnd());
514 Q_ASSERT(it.value());
515
516 return it;
517}
518
519// Go up the tree, creating mappings, unless of course the parent is filtered out
520IndexMap::const_iterator QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::create_mapping_recursive(const QModelIndex &source_parent) const
521{
522 if (source_parent.isValid()) {
523 const QModelIndex source_grand_parent = source_parent.parent();
524 IndexMap::const_iterator it = source_index_mapping.constFind(key: source_grand_parent);
525 IndexMap::const_iterator end = source_index_mapping.constEnd();
526 if (it == end) {
527 it = create_mapping_recursive(source_parent: source_grand_parent);
528 end = source_index_mapping.constEnd();
529 if (it == end)
530 return end;
531 }
532 Mapping *gm = it.value();
533 if (gm->proxy_rows.at(i: source_parent.row()) == -1 ||
534 gm->proxy_columns.at(i: source_parent.column()) == -1) {
535 // Can't do, parent is filtered
536 return end;
537 }
538 }
539 return create_mapping(source_parent);
540}
541
542QModelIndex QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::proxy_to_source(const QModelIndex &proxy_index) const
543{
544 if (!proxy_index.isValid())
545 return QModelIndex(); // for now; we may want to be able to set a root index later
546 if (proxy_index.model() != q_func()) {
547 qWarning(msg: "QSortFilterProxyModel: index from wrong model passed to mapToSource");
548 Q_ASSERT(!"QSortFilterProxyModel: index from wrong model passed to mapToSource");
549 return QModelIndex();
550 }
551 IndexMap::const_iterator it = index_to_iterator(proxy_index);
552 Mapping *m = it.value();
553 if ((proxy_index.row() >= m->source_rows.size()) || (proxy_index.column() >= m->source_columns.size()))
554 return QModelIndex();
555 int source_row = m->source_rows.at(i: proxy_index.row());
556 int source_col = m->source_columns.at(i: proxy_index.column());
557 return model->index(row: source_row, column: source_col, parent: it.key());
558}
559
560QModelIndex QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::source_to_proxy(const QModelIndex &source_index) const
561{
562 if (!source_index.isValid())
563 return QModelIndex(); // for now; we may want to be able to set a root index later
564 if (source_index.model() != model) {
565 qWarning(msg: "QSortFilterProxyModel: index from wrong model passed to mapFromSource");
566 Q_ASSERT(!"QSortFilterProxyModel: index from wrong model passed to mapFromSource");
567 return QModelIndex();
568 }
569 QModelIndex source_parent = source_index.parent();
570 IndexMap::const_iterator it = create_mapping(source_parent);
571 Mapping *m = it.value();
572 if ((source_index.row() >= m->proxy_rows.size()) || (source_index.column() >= m->proxy_columns.size()))
573 return QModelIndex();
574 int proxy_row = m->proxy_rows.at(i: source_index.row());
575 int proxy_column = m->proxy_columns.at(i: source_index.column());
576 if (proxy_row == -1 || proxy_column == -1)
577 return QModelIndex();
578 return create_index(row: proxy_row, column: proxy_column, it);
579}
580
581bool QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::can_create_mapping(const QModelIndex &source_parent) const
582{
583 if (source_parent.isValid()) {
584 QModelIndex source_grand_parent = source_parent.parent();
585 IndexMap::const_iterator it = source_index_mapping.constFind(key: source_grand_parent);
586 if (it == source_index_mapping.constEnd()) {
587 // Don't care, since we don't have mapping for the grand parent
588 return false;
589 }
590 Mapping *gm = it.value();
591 if (gm->proxy_rows.at(i: source_parent.row()) == -1 ||
592 gm->proxy_columns.at(i: source_parent.column()) == -1) {
593 // Don't care, since parent is filtered
594 return false;
595 }
596 }
597 return true;
598}

600/*!
601 \internal
602
603 Sorts the existing mappings.
604*/
605void QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::sort()
606{
607 Q_Q(QSortFilterProxyModel);
608 emit q->layoutAboutToBeChanged(parents: QList<QPersistentModelIndex>(), hint: QAbstractItemModel::VerticalSortHint);
609 QModelIndexPairList source_indexes = store_persistent_indexes();
610 const auto end = source_index_mapping.constEnd();
611 for (auto it = source_index_mapping.constBegin(); it != end; ++it) {
612 const QModelIndex &source_parent = it.key();
613 Mapping *m = it.value();
614 sort_source_rows(source_rows&: m->source_rows, source_parent);
615 build_source_to_proxy_mapping(proxy_to_source: m->source_rows, source_to_proxy&: m->proxy_rows);
616 }
617 update_persistent_indexes(source_indexes);
618 emit q->layoutChanged(parents: QList<QPersistentModelIndex>(), hint: QAbstractItemModel::VerticalSortHint);
619}
620
621/*!
622 \internal
623
624 update the source_sort_column according to the proxy_sort_column
625 return true if the column was changed
626*/
627bool QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::update_source_sort_column()
628{
629 int old_source_sort_column = source_sort_column;
630
631 if (proxy_sort_column == -1) {
632 source_sort_column = -1;
633 } else {
634 // We cannot use index mapping here because in case of a still-empty
635 // proxy model there's no valid proxy index we could map to source.
636 // So always use the root mapping directly instead.
637 Mapping *m = create_mapping(source_parent: QModelIndex()).value();
638 if (proxy_sort_column < m->source_columns.size())
639 source_sort_column = m->source_columns.at(i: proxy_sort_column);
640 else
641 source_sort_column = -1;
642 }
643
644 return old_source_sort_column != source_sort_column;
645}
646
647/*!
648 \internal
649
650 Find the source_sort_column without creating a full mapping and
651 without updating anything.
652*/
653int QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::find_source_sort_column() const
654{
655 if (proxy_sort_column == -1)
656 return -1;
657
658 const QModelIndex rootIndex;
659 const int source_cols = model->columnCount();
660 int accepted_columns = -1;
661
662 Q_Q(const QSortFilterProxyModel);
663 for (int i = 0; i < source_cols; ++i) {
664 if (q->filterAcceptsColumn(source_column: i, source_parent: rootIndex)) {
665 if (++accepted_columns == proxy_sort_column)
666 return i;
667 }
668 }
669
670 return -1;
671}
672
673/*!
674 \internal
675
676 Sorts the given \a source_rows according to current sort column and order.
677*/
678void QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::sort_source_rows(
679 QList<int> &source_rows, const QModelIndex &source_parent) const
680{
681 Q_Q(const QSortFilterProxyModel);
682 if (source_sort_column >= 0) {
683 if (sort_order == Qt::AscendingOrder) {
684 QSortFilterProxyModelLessThan lt(source_sort_column, source_parent, model, q);
685 std::stable_sort(first: source_rows.begin(), last: source_rows.end(), comp: lt);
686 } else {
687 QSortFilterProxyModelGreaterThan gt(source_sort_column, source_parent, model, q);
688 std::stable_sort(first: source_rows.begin(), last: source_rows.end(), comp: gt);
689 }
690 } else { // restore the source model order
691 std::stable_sort(first: source_rows.begin(), last: source_rows.end());
692 }
693}

695/*!
696 \internal
697
698 Given source-to-proxy mapping \a source_to_proxy and the set of
699 source items \a source_items (which are part of that mapping),
700 determines the corresponding proxy item intervals that should
701 be removed from the proxy model.
702
703 The result is a vector of pairs, where each pair represents a
704 (start, end) tuple, sorted in ascending order.
705*/
706QList<QPair<int, int>> QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::proxy_intervals_for_source_items(
707 const QList<int> &source_to_proxy, const QList<int> &source_items) const
708{
709 QList<QPair<int, int>> proxy_intervals;
710 if (source_items.isEmpty())
711 return proxy_intervals;
712
713 int source_items_index = 0;
714 while (source_items_index < source_items.size()) {
715 int first_proxy_item = source_to_proxy.at(i: source_items.at(i: source_items_index));
716 Q_ASSERT(first_proxy_item != -1);
717 int last_proxy_item = first_proxy_item;
718 ++source_items_index;
719 // Find end of interval
720 while ((source_items_index < source_items.size())
721 && (source_to_proxy.at(i: source_items.at(i: source_items_index)) == last_proxy_item + 1)) {
722 ++last_proxy_item;
723 ++source_items_index;
724 }
725 // Add interval to result
726 proxy_intervals.append(t: QPair<int, int>(first_proxy_item, last_proxy_item));
727 }
728 std::stable_sort(first: proxy_intervals.begin(), last: proxy_intervals.end());
729 // Consolidate adjacent intervals
730 for (int i = proxy_intervals.size()-1; i > 0; --i) {
731 QPair<int, int> &interval = proxy_intervals[i];
732 QPair<int, int> &preceeding_interval = proxy_intervals[i - 1];
733 if (interval.first == preceeding_interval.second + 1) {
734 preceeding_interval.second = interval.second;
735 interval.first = interval.second = -1;
736 }
737 }
738 proxy_intervals.removeIf(pred: [](QPair<int, int> interval) { return interval.first < 0; });
739 return proxy_intervals;
740}
741
742/*!
743 \internal
744
745 Given source-to-proxy mapping \a src_to_proxy and proxy-to-source mapping
746 \a proxy_to_source, removes \a source_items from this proxy model.
747 The corresponding proxy items are removed in intervals, so that the proper
748 rows/columnsRemoved(start, end) signals will be generated.
749*/
750void QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::remove_source_items(
751 QList<int> &source_to_proxy, QList<int> &proxy_to_source,
752 const QList<int> &source_items, const QModelIndex &source_parent,
753 Qt::Orientation orient, bool emit_signal)
754{
755 Q_Q(QSortFilterProxyModel);
756 QModelIndex proxy_parent = q->mapFromSource(sourceIndex: source_parent);
757 if (!proxy_parent.isValid() && source_parent.isValid()) {
758 proxy_to_source.clear();
759 return; // nothing to do (already removed)
760 }
761
762 const auto proxy_intervals = proxy_intervals_for_source_items(
763 source_to_proxy, source_items);
764
765 const auto end = proxy_intervals.rend();
766 for (auto it = proxy_intervals.rbegin(); it != end; ++it) {
767 const QPair<int, int> &interval = *it;
768 const int proxy_start = interval.first;
769 const int proxy_end = interval.second;
770 remove_proxy_interval(source_to_proxy, proxy_to_source, proxy_start, proxy_end,
771 proxy_parent, orient, emit_signal);
772 }
773}
774
775/*!
776 \internal
777
778 Given source-to-proxy mapping \a source_to_proxy and proxy-to-source mapping
779 \a proxy_to_source, removes items from \a proxy_start to \a proxy_end
780 (inclusive) from this proxy model.
781*/
782void QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::remove_proxy_interval(
783 QList<int> &source_to_proxy, QList<int> &proxy_to_source, int proxy_start, int proxy_end,
784 const QModelIndex &proxy_parent, Qt::Orientation orient, bool emit_signal)
785{
786 Q_Q(QSortFilterProxyModel);
787 if (emit_signal) {
788 if (orient == Qt::Vertical)
789 q->beginRemoveRows(parent: proxy_parent, first: proxy_start, last: proxy_end);
790 else
791 q->beginRemoveColumns(parent: proxy_parent, first: proxy_start, last: proxy_end);
792 }
793
794 // Remove items from proxy-to-source mapping
795 for (int i = proxy_start; i <= proxy_end; ++i)
796 source_to_proxy[proxy_to_source.at(i)] = -1;
797 proxy_to_source.remove(i: proxy_start, n: proxy_end - proxy_start + 1);
798
799 build_source_to_proxy_mapping(proxy_to_source, source_to_proxy, start: proxy_start);
800
801 if (emit_signal) {
802 if (orient == Qt::Vertical)
803 q->endRemoveRows();
804 else
805 q->endRemoveColumns();
806 }
807}
808
809/*!
810 \internal
811
812 Given proxy-to-source mapping \a proxy_to_source and a set of
813 unmapped source items \a source_items, determines the proxy item
814 intervals at which the subsets of source items should be inserted
815 (but does not actually add them to the mapping).
816
817 The result is a vector of pairs, each pair representing a tuple (start,
818 items), where items is a vector containing the (sorted) source items that
819 should be inserted at that proxy model location.
820*/
821QList<QPair<int, QList<int>>> QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::proxy_intervals_for_source_items_to_add(
822 const QList<int> &proxy_to_source, const QList<int> &source_items,
823 const QModelIndex &source_parent, Qt::Orientation orient) const
824{
825 Q_Q(const QSortFilterProxyModel);
826 QList<QPair<int, QList<int>>> proxy_intervals;
827 if (source_items.isEmpty())
828 return proxy_intervals;
829
830 int proxy_low = 0;
831 int proxy_item = 0;
832 int source_items_index = 0;
833 QList<int> source_items_in_interval;
834 bool compare = (orient == Qt::Vertical && source_sort_column >= 0 && dynamic_sortfilter);
835 while (source_items_index < source_items.size()) {
836 source_items_in_interval.clear();
837 int first_new_source_item = source_items.at(i: source_items_index);
838 source_items_in_interval.append(t: first_new_source_item);
839 ++source_items_index;
840
841 // Find proxy item at which insertion should be started
842 int proxy_high = proxy_to_source.size() - 1;
843 QModelIndex i1 = compare ? model->index(row: first_new_source_item, column: source_sort_column, parent: source_parent) : QModelIndex();
844 while (proxy_low <= proxy_high) {
845 proxy_item = (proxy_low + proxy_high) / 2;
846 if (compare) {
847 QModelIndex i2 = model->index(row: proxy_to_source.at(i: proxy_item), column: source_sort_column, parent: source_parent);
848 if ((sort_order == Qt::AscendingOrder) ? q->lessThan(source_left: i1, source_right: i2) : q->lessThan(source_left: i2, source_right: i1))
849 proxy_high = proxy_item - 1;
850 else
851 proxy_low = proxy_item + 1;
852 } else {
853 if (first_new_source_item < proxy_to_source.at(i: proxy_item))
854 proxy_high = proxy_item - 1;
855 else
856 proxy_low = proxy_item + 1;
857 }
858 }
859 proxy_item = proxy_low;
860
861 // Find the sequence of new source items that should be inserted here
862 if (proxy_item >= proxy_to_source.size()) {
863 for ( ; source_items_index < source_items.size(); ++source_items_index)
864 source_items_in_interval.append(t: source_items.at(i: source_items_index));
865 } else {
866 i1 = compare ? model->index(row: proxy_to_source.at(i: proxy_item), column: source_sort_column, parent: source_parent) : QModelIndex();
867 for ( ; source_items_index < source_items.size(); ++source_items_index) {
868 int new_source_item = source_items.at(i: source_items_index);
869 if (compare) {
870 QModelIndex i2 = model->index(row: new_source_item, column: source_sort_column, parent: source_parent);
871 if ((sort_order == Qt::AscendingOrder) ? q->lessThan(source_left: i1, source_right: i2) : q->lessThan(source_left: i2, source_right: i1))
872 break;
873 } else {
874 if (proxy_to_source.at(i: proxy_item) < new_source_item)
875 break;
876 }
877 source_items_in_interval.append(t: new_source_item);
878 }
879 }
880
881 // Add interval to result
882 proxy_intervals.append(t: QPair<int, QList<int>>(proxy_item, source_items_in_interval));
883 }
884 return proxy_intervals;
885}

887/*!
888 \internal
889
890 Given source-to-proxy mapping \a source_to_proxy and proxy-to-source mapping
891 \a proxy_to_source, inserts the given \a source_items into this proxy model.
892 The source items are inserted in intervals (based on some sorted order), so
893 that the proper rows/columnsInserted(start, end) signals will be generated.
894*/
895void QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::insert_source_items(
896 QList<int> &source_to_proxy, QList<int> &proxy_to_source,
897 const QList<int> &source_items, const QModelIndex &source_parent,
898 Qt::Orientation orient, bool emit_signal)
899{
900 Q_Q(QSortFilterProxyModel);
901 QModelIndex proxy_parent = q->mapFromSource(sourceIndex: source_parent);
902 if (!proxy_parent.isValid() && source_parent.isValid())
903 return; // nothing to do (source_parent is not mapped)
904
905 const auto proxy_intervals = proxy_intervals_for_source_items_to_add(
906 proxy_to_source, source_items, source_parent, orient);
907
908 const auto end = proxy_intervals.rend();
909 for (auto it = proxy_intervals.rbegin(); it != end; ++it) {
910 const QPair<int, QList<int>> &interval = *it;
911 const int proxy_start = interval.first;
912 const QList<int> &source_items = interval.second;
913 const int proxy_end = proxy_start + source_items.size() - 1;
914
915 if (emit_signal) {
916 if (orient == Qt::Vertical)
917 q->beginInsertRows(parent: proxy_parent, first: proxy_start, last: proxy_end);
918 else
919 q->beginInsertColumns(parent: proxy_parent, first: proxy_start, last: proxy_end);
920 }
921
922 // TODO: use the range QList::insert() overload once it is implemented (QTBUG-58633).
923 proxy_to_source.insert(i: proxy_start, n: source_items.size(), t: 0);
924 std::copy(source_items.cbegin(), source_items.cend(), proxy_to_source.begin() + proxy_start);
925
926 build_source_to_proxy_mapping(proxy_to_source, source_to_proxy, start: proxy_start);
927
928 if (emit_signal) {
929 if (orient == Qt::Vertical)
930 q->endInsertRows();
931 else
932 q->endInsertColumns();
933 }
934 }
935}
936
937/*!
938 \internal
939
940 Handles source model items insertion (columnsInserted(), rowsInserted()).
941 Determines
942 1) which of the inserted items to also insert into proxy model (filtering),
943 2) where to insert the items into the proxy model (sorting),
944 then inserts those items.
945 The items are inserted into the proxy model in intervals (based on
946 sorted order), so that the proper rows/columnsInserted(start, end)
947 signals will be generated.
948*/
949void QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::source_items_inserted(
950 const QModelIndex &source_parent, int start, int end, Qt::Orientation orient)
951{
952 Q_Q(QSortFilterProxyModel);
953 if ((start < 0) || (end < 0))
954 return;
955 IndexMap::const_iterator it = source_index_mapping.constFind(key: source_parent);
956 if (it == source_index_mapping.constEnd()) {
957 if (!can_create_mapping(source_parent))
958 return;
959 it = create_mapping(source_parent);
960 Mapping *m = it.value();
961 QModelIndex proxy_parent = q->mapFromSource(sourceIndex: source_parent);
962 if (m->source_rows.size() > 0) {
963 q->beginInsertRows(parent: proxy_parent, first: 0, last: m->source_rows.size() - 1);
964 q->endInsertRows();
965 }
966 if (m->source_columns.size() > 0) {
967 q->beginInsertColumns(parent: proxy_parent, first: 0, last: m->source_columns.size() - 1);
968 q->endInsertColumns();
969 }
970 return;
971 }
972
973 Mapping *m = it.value();
974 QList<int> &source_to_proxy = (orient == Qt::Vertical) ? m->proxy_rows : m->proxy_columns;
975 QList<int> &proxy_to_source = (orient == Qt::Vertical) ? m->source_rows : m->source_columns;
976
977 int delta_item_count = end - start + 1;
978 int old_item_count = source_to_proxy.size();
979
980 updateChildrenMapping(source_parent, parent_mapping: m, orient, start, end, delta_item_count, remove: false);
981
982 // Expand source-to-proxy mapping to account for new items
983 if (start < 0 || start > source_to_proxy.size()) {
984 qWarning(msg: "QSortFilterProxyModel: invalid inserted rows reported by source model");
985 remove_from_mapping(source_parent);
986 return;
987 }
988 source_to_proxy.insert(i: start, n: delta_item_count, t: -1);
989
990 if (start < old_item_count) {
991 // Adjust existing "stale" indexes in proxy-to-source mapping
992 int proxy_count = proxy_to_source.size();
993 for (int proxy_item = 0; proxy_item < proxy_count; ++proxy_item) {
994 int source_item = proxy_to_source.at(i: proxy_item);
995 if (source_item >= start)
996 proxy_to_source.replace(i: proxy_item, t: source_item + delta_item_count);
997 }
998 build_source_to_proxy_mapping(proxy_to_source, source_to_proxy);
999 }
1000
1001 // Figure out which items to add to mapping based on filter
1002 QList<int> source_items;
1003 for (int i = start; i <= end; ++i) {
1004 if ((orient == Qt::Vertical)
1005 ? filterAcceptsRowInternal(source_row: i, source_parent)
1006 : q->filterAcceptsColumn(source_column: i, source_parent)) {
1007 source_items.append(t: i);
1008 }
1009 }
1010
1011 if (model->rowCount(parent: source_parent) == delta_item_count) {
1012 // Items were inserted where there were none before.
1013 // If it was new rows make sure to create mappings for columns so that a
1014 // valid mapping can be retrieved later and vice-versa.
1015
1016 QList<int> &orthogonal_proxy_to_source = (orient == Qt::Horizontal) ? m->source_rows : m->source_columns;
1017 QList<int> &orthogonal_source_to_proxy = (orient == Qt::Horizontal) ? m->proxy_rows : m->proxy_columns;
1018
1019 if (orthogonal_source_to_proxy.isEmpty()) {
1020 const int ortho_end = (orient == Qt::Horizontal) ? model->rowCount(parent: source_parent) : model->columnCount(parent: source_parent);
1021
1022 orthogonal_source_to_proxy.resize(size: ortho_end);
1023
1024 for (int ortho_item = 0; ortho_item < ortho_end; ++ortho_item) {
1025 if ((orient == Qt::Horizontal) ? filterAcceptsRowInternal(source_row: ortho_item, source_parent)
1026 : q->filterAcceptsColumn(source_column: ortho_item, source_parent)) {
1027 orthogonal_proxy_to_source.append(t: ortho_item);
1028 }
1029 }
1030 if (orient == Qt::Horizontal) {
1031 // We're reacting to columnsInserted, but we've just inserted new rows. Sort them.
1032 sort_source_rows(source_rows&: orthogonal_proxy_to_source, source_parent);
1033 }
1034 build_source_to_proxy_mapping(proxy_to_source: orthogonal_proxy_to_source, source_to_proxy&: orthogonal_source_to_proxy);
1035 }
1036 }
1037
1038 // Sort and insert the items
1039 if (orient == Qt::Vertical) // Only sort rows
1040 sort_source_rows(source_rows&: source_items, source_parent);
1041 insert_source_items(source_to_proxy, proxy_to_source, source_items, source_parent, orient);
1042}

1044/*!
1045 \internal
1046
1047 Handles source model items removal
1048 (columnsAboutToBeRemoved(), rowsAboutToBeRemoved()).
1049*/
1050void QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::source_items_about_to_be_removed(
1051 const QModelIndex &source_parent, int start, int end, Qt::Orientation orient)
1052{
1053 if ((start < 0) || (end < 0))
1054 return;
1055 IndexMap::const_iterator it = source_index_mapping.constFind(key: source_parent);
1056 if (it == source_index_mapping.constEnd()) {
1057 // Don't care, since we don't have mapping for this index
1058 return;
1059 }
1060
1061 Mapping *m = it.value();
1062 QList<int> &source_to_proxy = (orient == Qt::Vertical) ? m->proxy_rows : m->proxy_columns;
1063 QList<int> &proxy_to_source = (orient == Qt::Vertical) ? m->source_rows : m->source_columns;
1064
1065 // figure out which items to remove
1066 QList<int> source_items_to_remove;
1067 int proxy_count = proxy_to_source.size();
1068 for (int proxy_item = 0; proxy_item < proxy_count; ++proxy_item) {
1069 int source_item = proxy_to_source.at(i: proxy_item);
1070 if ((source_item >= start) && (source_item <= end))
1071 source_items_to_remove.append(t: source_item);
1072 }
1073
1074 remove_source_items(source_to_proxy, proxy_to_source, source_items: source_items_to_remove,
1075 source_parent, orient);
1076}

1078/*!
1079 \internal
1080
1081 Handles source model items removal (columnsRemoved(), rowsRemoved()).
1082*/
1083void QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::source_items_removed(
1084 const QModelIndex &source_parent, int start, int end, Qt::Orientation orient)
1085{
1086 if ((start < 0) || (end < 0))
1087 return;
1088 IndexMap::const_iterator it = source_index_mapping.constFind(key: source_parent);
1089 if (it == source_index_mapping.constEnd()) {
1090 // Don't care, since we don't have mapping for this index
1091 return;
1092 }
1093
1094 Mapping *m = it.value();
1095 QList<int> &source_to_proxy = (orient == Qt::Vertical) ? m->proxy_rows : m->proxy_columns;
1096 QList<int> &proxy_to_source = (orient == Qt::Vertical) ? m->source_rows : m->source_columns;
1097
1098 if (end >= source_to_proxy.size())
1099 end = source_to_proxy.size() - 1;
1100
1101 // Shrink the source-to-proxy mapping to reflect the new item count
1102 int delta_item_count = end - start + 1;
1103 source_to_proxy.remove(i: start, n: delta_item_count);
1104
1105 int proxy_count = proxy_to_source.size();
1106 if (proxy_count > source_to_proxy.size()) {
1107 // mapping is in an inconsistent state -- redo the whole mapping
1108 qWarning(msg: "QSortFilterProxyModel: inconsistent changes reported by source model");
1109 Q_Q(QSortFilterProxyModel);
1110 q->beginResetModel();
1111 remove_from_mapping(source_parent);
1112 q->endResetModel();
1113 return;
1114 }
1115
1116 // Adjust "stale" indexes in proxy-to-source mapping
1117 for (int proxy_item = 0; proxy_item < proxy_count; ++proxy_item) {
1118 int source_item = proxy_to_source.at(i: proxy_item);
1119 if (source_item >= start) {
1120 Q_ASSERT(source_item - delta_item_count >= 0);
1121 proxy_to_source.replace(i: proxy_item, t: source_item - delta_item_count);
1122 }
1123 }
1124 build_source_to_proxy_mapping(proxy_to_source, source_to_proxy);
1125
1126 updateChildrenMapping(source_parent, parent_mapping: m, orient, start, end, delta_item_count, remove: true);
1127
1128}
1129
1130
1131/*!
1132 \internal
1133 updates the mapping of the children when inserting or removing items
1134*/
1135void QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::updateChildrenMapping(const QModelIndex &source_parent, Mapping *parent_mapping,
1136 Qt::Orientation orient, int start, int end, int delta_item_count, bool remove)
1137{
1138 // see if any mapped children should be (re)moved
1139 QList<QPair<QModelIndex, Mapping *>> moved_source_index_mappings;
1140 auto it2 = parent_mapping->mapped_children.begin();
1141 for ( ; it2 != parent_mapping->mapped_children.end();) {
1142 const QModelIndex source_child_index = *it2;
1143 const int pos = (orient == Qt::Vertical)
1144 ? source_child_index.row()
1145 : source_child_index.column();
1146 if (pos < start) {
1147 // not affected
1148 ++it2;
1149 } else if (remove && pos <= end) {
1150 // in the removed interval
1151 it2 = parent_mapping->mapped_children.erase(pos: it2);
1152 remove_from_mapping(source_parent: source_child_index);
1153 } else {
1154 // below the removed items -- recompute the index
1155 QModelIndex new_index;
1156 const int newpos = remove ? pos - delta_item_count : pos + delta_item_count;
1157 if (orient == Qt::Vertical) {
1158 new_index = model->index(row: newpos,
1159 column: source_child_index.column(),
1160 parent: source_parent);
1161 } else {
1162 new_index = model->index(row: source_child_index.row(),
1163 column: newpos,
1164 parent: source_parent);
1165 }
1166 *it2 = new_index;
1167 ++it2;
1168
1169 // update mapping
1170 Mapping *cm = source_index_mapping.take(key: source_child_index);
1171 Q_ASSERT(cm);
1172 // we do not reinsert right away, because the new index might be identical with another, old index
1173 moved_source_index_mappings.append(t: QPair<QModelIndex, Mapping*>(new_index, cm));
1174 }
1175 }
1176
1177 // reinsert moved, mapped indexes
1178 for (auto &pair : std::as_const(t&: moved_source_index_mappings)) {
1179 pair.second->source_parent = pair.first;
1180 source_index_mapping.insert(key: pair.first, value: pair.second);
1181 }

1190{
1191 proxy_low = INT_MAX;

1199 proxy_high = proxy_item;

1274
1275/*!
1276 \internal
1277
1278 Updates the proxy model (adds/removes rows) based on the
1279 new filter.
1280*/
1281void QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::filter_changed(Direction dir, const QModelIndex &source_parent)
1282{
1283 IndexMap::const_iterator it = source_index_mapping.constFind(key: source_parent);
1284 if (it == source_index_mapping.constEnd())
1285 return;
1286 Mapping *m = it.value();
1287 const QSet<int> rows_removed = (dir & Direction::Rows) ? handle_filter_changed(source_to_proxy&: m->proxy_rows, proxy_to_source&: m->source_rows, source_parent, orient: Qt::Vertical) : QSet<int>();
1288 const QSet<int> columns_removed = (dir & Direction::Columns) ? handle_filter_changed(source_to_proxy&: m->proxy_columns, proxy_to_source&: m->source_columns, source_parent, orient: Qt::Horizontal) : QSet<int>();
1289
1290 // We need to iterate over a copy of m->mapped_children because otherwise it may be changed by other code, invalidating
1291 // the iterator it2.
1292 // The m->mapped_children vector can be appended to with indexes which are no longer filtered
1293 // out (in create_mapping) when this function recurses for child indexes.
1294 const QList<QModelIndex> mappedChildren = m->mapped_children;
1295 QList<int> indexesToRemove;
1296 for (int i = 0; i < mappedChildren.size(); ++i) {
1297 const QModelIndex &source_child_index = mappedChildren.at(i);
1298 if (rows_removed.contains(value: source_child_index.row()) || columns_removed.contains(value: source_child_index.column())) {
1299 indexesToRemove.push_back(t: i);
1300 remove_from_mapping(source_parent: source_child_index);
1301 } else {
1302 filter_changed(dir, source_parent: source_child_index);
1303 }
1304 }
1305 QList<int>::const_iterator removeIt = indexesToRemove.constEnd();
1306 const QList<int>::const_iterator removeBegin = indexesToRemove.constBegin();
1307
1308 // We can't just remove these items from mappedChildren while iterating above and then
1309 // do something like m->mapped_children = mappedChildren, because mapped_children might
1310 // be appended to in create_mapping, and we would lose those new items.
1311 // Because they are always appended in create_mapping, we can still remove them by
1312 // position here.
1313 while (removeIt != removeBegin) {
1314 --removeIt;
1315 m->mapped_children.remove(i: *removeIt);
1316 }
1317}
1318
1319/*!
1320 \internal
1321 returns the removed items indexes
1322*/
1323QSet<int> QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::handle_filter_changed(
1324 QList<int> &source_to_proxy, QList<int> &proxy_to_source,
1325 const QModelIndex &source_parent, Qt::Orientation orient)
1326{
1327 Q_Q(QSortFilterProxyModel);
1328 // Figure out which mapped items to remove
1329 QList<int> source_items_remove;
1330 for (int i = 0; i < proxy_to_source.size(); ++i) {
1331 const int source_item = proxy_to_source.at(i);
1332 if ((orient == Qt::Vertical)
1333 ? !filterAcceptsRowInternal(source_row: source_item, source_parent)
1334 : !q->filterAcceptsColumn(source_column: source_item, source_parent)) {
1335 // This source item does not satisfy the filter, so it must be removed
1336 source_items_remove.append(t: source_item);
1337 }
1338 }
1339 // Figure out which non-mapped items to insert
1340 QList<int> source_items_insert;
1341 int source_count = source_to_proxy.size();
1342 for (int source_item = 0; source_item < source_count; ++source_item) {
1343 if (source_to_proxy.at(i: source_item) == -1) {
1344 if ((orient == Qt::Vertical)
1345 ? filterAcceptsRowInternal(source_row: source_item, source_parent)
1346 : q->filterAcceptsColumn(source_column: source_item, source_parent)) {
1347 // This source item satisfies the filter, so it must be added
1348 source_items_insert.append(t: source_item);
1349 }
1350 }
1351 }
1352 if (!source_items_remove.isEmpty() || !source_items_insert.isEmpty()) {
1353 // Do item removal and insertion
1354 remove_source_items(source_to_proxy, proxy_to_source,
1355 source_items: source_items_remove, source_parent, orient);
1356 if (orient == Qt::Vertical)
1357 sort_source_rows(source_rows&: source_items_insert, source_parent);
1358 insert_source_items(source_to_proxy, proxy_to_source,
1359 source_items: source_items_insert, source_parent, orient);
1360 }
1361 return qListToSet(vector: source_items_remove);
1362}
1363
1364bool QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::needsReorder(const QList<int> &source_rows, const QModelIndex &source_parent) const
1365{
1366 Q_Q(const QSortFilterProxyModel);
1367 Q_ASSERT(source_sort_column != -1);
1368 const int proxyRowCount = q->rowCount(parent: source_to_proxy(source_index: source_parent));
1369 // If any modified proxy row no longer passes lessThan(previous, current) or lessThan(current, next) then we need to reorder.
1370 return std::any_of(first: source_rows.begin(), last: source_rows.end(),
1371 pred: [this, q, proxyRowCount, source_parent](int sourceRow) -> bool {
1372 const QModelIndex sourceIndex = model->index(row: sourceRow, column: source_sort_column, parent: source_parent);
1373 const QModelIndex proxyIndex = source_to_proxy(source_index: sourceIndex);
1374 Q_ASSERT(proxyIndex.isValid()); // caller ensured source_rows were not filtered out
1375 if (proxyIndex.row() > 0) {
1376 const QModelIndex prevProxyIndex = q->sibling(row: proxyIndex.row() - 1, column: proxy_sort_column, idx: proxyIndex);
1377 const QModelIndex prevSourceIndex = proxy_to_source(proxy_index: prevProxyIndex);
1378 if (sort_order == Qt::AscendingOrder ? q->lessThan(source_left: sourceIndex, source_right: prevSourceIndex) : q->lessThan(source_left: prevSourceIndex, source_right: sourceIndex))
1379 return true;
1380 }
1381 if (proxyIndex.row() < proxyRowCount - 1) {
1382 const QModelIndex nextProxyIndex = q->sibling(row: proxyIndex.row() + 1, column: proxy_sort_column, idx: proxyIndex);
1383 const QModelIndex nextSourceIndex = proxy_to_source(proxy_index: nextProxyIndex);
1384 if (sort_order == Qt::AscendingOrder ? q->lessThan(source_left: nextSourceIndex, source_right: sourceIndex) : q->lessThan(source_left: sourceIndex, source_right: nextSourceIndex))
1385 return true;
1386 }
1387 return false;
1388 });
1389}
1390
1391void QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::_q_sourceDataChanged(const QModelIndex &source_top_left,
1392 const QModelIndex &source_bottom_right,
1393 const QList<int> &roles)
1394{
1395 Q_Q(QSortFilterProxyModel);
1396 if (!source_top_left.isValid() || !source_bottom_right.isValid())
1397 return;
1398
1399 std::vector<QSortFilterProxyModelDataChanged> data_changed_list;
1400 data_changed_list.emplace_back(args: source_top_left, args: source_bottom_right);
1401
1402 // Do check parents if the filter role have changed and we are recursive
1403 if (filter_recursive && (roles.isEmpty() || roles.contains(t: filter_role))) {
1404 QModelIndex source_parent = source_top_left.parent();
1405
1406 while (source_parent.isValid()) {
1407 data_changed_list.emplace_back(args&: source_parent, args&: source_parent);
1408 source_parent = source_parent.parent();
1409 }
1410 }
1411
1412 for (const QSortFilterProxyModelDataChanged &data_changed : data_changed_list) {
1413 const QModelIndex &source_top_left = data_changed.topLeft;
1414 const QModelIndex &source_bottom_right = data_changed.bottomRight;
1415 const QModelIndex source_parent = source_top_left.parent();
1416
1417 bool change_in_unmapped_parent = false;
1418 IndexMap::const_iterator it = source_index_mapping.constFind(key: source_parent);
1419 if (it == source_index_mapping.constEnd()) {
1420 // We don't have mapping for this index, so we cannot know how things
1421 // changed (in case the change affects filtering) in order to forward
1422 // the change correctly.
1423 // But we can at least forward the signal "as is", if the row isn't
1424 // filtered out, this is better than nothing.
1425 it = create_mapping_recursive(source_parent);
1426 if (it == source_index_mapping.constEnd())
1427 continue;
1428 change_in_unmapped_parent = true;
1429 }
1430
1431 Mapping *m = it.value();
1432
1433 // Figure out how the source changes affect us
1434 QList<int> source_rows_remove;
1435 QList<int> source_rows_insert;
1436 QList<int> source_rows_change;
1437 QList<int> source_rows_resort;
1438 int end = qMin(a: source_bottom_right.row(), b: m->proxy_rows.size() - 1);
1439 for (int source_row = source_top_left.row(); source_row <= end; ++source_row) {
1440 if (dynamic_sortfilter && !change_in_unmapped_parent) {
1441 if (m->proxy_rows.at(i: source_row) != -1) {
1442 if (!filterAcceptsRowInternal(source_row, source_parent)) {
1443 // This source row no longer satisfies the filter, so it must be removed
1444 source_rows_remove.append(t: source_row);
1445 } else if (source_sort_column >= source_top_left.column() && source_sort_column <= source_bottom_right.column()) {
1446 // This source row has changed in a way that may affect sorted order
1447 source_rows_resort.append(t: source_row);
1448 } else {
1449 // This row has simply changed, without affecting filtering nor sorting
1450 source_rows_change.append(t: source_row);
1451 }
1452 } else {
1453 if (!itemsBeingRemoved.contains(parent: source_parent, row: source_row) && filterAcceptsRowInternal(source_row, source_parent)) {
1454 // This source row now satisfies the filter, so it must be added
1455 source_rows_insert.append(t: source_row);
1456 }
1457 }
1458 } else {
1459 if (m->proxy_rows.at(i: source_row) != -1)
1460 source_rows_change.append(t: source_row);
1461 }
1462 }
1463
1464 if (!source_rows_remove.isEmpty()) {
1465 remove_source_items(source_to_proxy&: m->proxy_rows, proxy_to_source&: m->source_rows,
1466 source_items: source_rows_remove, source_parent, orient: Qt::Vertical);
1467 QSet<int> source_rows_remove_set = qListToSet(vector: source_rows_remove);
1468 QList<QModelIndex>::iterator childIt = m->mapped_children.end();
1469 while (childIt != m->mapped_children.begin()) {
1470 --childIt;
1471 const QModelIndex source_child_index = *childIt;
1472 if (source_rows_remove_set.contains(value: source_child_index.row())) {
1473 childIt = m->mapped_children.erase(pos: childIt);
1474 remove_from_mapping(source_parent: source_child_index);
1475 }
1476 }
1477 }
1478
1479 if (!source_rows_resort.isEmpty()) {
1480 if (needsReorder(source_rows: source_rows_resort, source_parent)) {
1481 // Re-sort the rows of this level
1482 QList<QPersistentModelIndex> parents;
1483 parents << q->mapFromSource(sourceIndex: source_parent);
1484 emit q->layoutAboutToBeChanged(parents, hint: QAbstractItemModel::VerticalSortHint);
1485 QModelIndexPairList source_indexes = store_persistent_indexes();
1486 remove_source_items(source_to_proxy&: m->proxy_rows, proxy_to_source&: m->source_rows, source_items: source_rows_resort,
1487 source_parent, orient: Qt::Vertical, emit_signal: false);
1488 sort_source_rows(source_rows&: source_rows_resort, source_parent);
1489 insert_source_items(source_to_proxy&: m->proxy_rows, proxy_to_source&: m->source_rows, source_items: source_rows_resort,
1490 source_parent, orient: Qt::Vertical, emit_signal: false);
1491 update_persistent_indexes(source_indexes);
1492 emit q->layoutChanged(parents, hint: QAbstractItemModel::VerticalSortHint);
1493 }
1494 // Make sure we also emit dataChanged for the rows
1495 source_rows_change += source_rows_resort;
1496 }
1497
1498 if (!source_rows_change.isEmpty()) {
1499 // Find the proxy row range
1500 int proxy_start_row;
1501 int proxy_end_row;
1502 proxy_item_range(source_to_proxy: m->proxy_rows, source_items: source_rows_change,
1503 proxy_low&: proxy_start_row, proxy_high&: proxy_end_row);
1504 // ### Find the proxy column range also
1505 if (proxy_end_row >= 0) {
1506 // the row was accepted, but some columns might still be filtered out
1507 int source_left_column = source_top_left.column();
1508 while (source_left_column < source_bottom_right.column()
1509 && m->proxy_columns.at(i: source_left_column) == -1)
1510 ++source_left_column;
1511 if (m->proxy_columns.at(i: source_left_column) != -1) {
1512 const QModelIndex proxy_top_left = create_index(
1513 row: proxy_start_row, column: m->proxy_columns.at(i: source_left_column), it);
1514 int source_right_column = source_bottom_right.column();
1515 while (source_right_column > source_top_left.column()
1516 && m->proxy_columns.at(i: source_right_column) == -1)
1517 --source_right_column;
1518 if (m->proxy_columns.at(i: source_right_column) != -1) {
1519 const QModelIndex proxy_bottom_right = create_index(
1520 row: proxy_end_row, column: m->proxy_columns.at(i: source_right_column), it);
1521 emit q->dataChanged(topLeft: proxy_top_left, bottomRight: proxy_bottom_right, roles);
1522 }
1523 }
1524 }
1525 }
1526
1527 if (!source_rows_insert.isEmpty()) {
1528 sort_source_rows(source_rows&: source_rows_insert, source_parent);
1529 insert_source_items(source_to_proxy&: m->proxy_rows, proxy_to_source&: m->source_rows,
1530 source_items: source_rows_insert, source_parent, orient: Qt::Vertical);
1531 }
1532 }
1533}

1535void QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::_q_sourceHeaderDataChanged(Qt::Orientation orientation,
1536 int start, int end)
1537{
1538 Q_ASSERT(start <= end);
1539
1540 Q_Q(QSortFilterProxyModel);
1541 Mapping *m = create_mapping(source_parent: QModelIndex()).value();
1542
1543 const QList<int> &source_to_proxy = (orientation == Qt::Vertical) ? m->proxy_rows : m->proxy_columns;
1544
1545 QList<int> proxy_positions;
1546 proxy_positions.reserve(size: end - start + 1);
1547 {
1548 Q_ASSERT(source_to_proxy.size() > end);
1549 QList<int>::const_iterator it = source_to_proxy.constBegin() + start;
1550 const QList<int>::const_iterator endIt = source_to_proxy.constBegin() + end + 1;
1551 for ( ; it != endIt; ++it) {
1552 if (*it != -1)
1553 proxy_positions.push_back(t: *it);
1554 }
1555 }
1556
1557 std::sort(first: proxy_positions.begin(), last: proxy_positions.end());
1558
1559 int last_index = 0;
1560 const int numItems = proxy_positions.size();
1561 while (last_index < numItems) {
1562 const int proxyStart = proxy_positions.at(i: last_index);
1563 int proxyEnd = proxyStart;
1564 ++last_index;
1565 for (int i = last_index; i < numItems; ++i) {
1566 if (proxy_positions.at(i) == proxyEnd + 1) {
1567 ++last_index;
1568 ++proxyEnd;
1569 } else {
1570 break;
1571 }
1572 }
1573 emit q->headerDataChanged(orientation, first: proxyStart, last: proxyEnd);
1574 }
1575}

1600 saved_layoutChange_parents.clear();

1646void QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::_q_sourceRowsAboutToBeInserted(
1647 const QModelIndex &source_parent, int start, int end)
1648{
1649 Q_UNUSED(start);
1650 Q_UNUSED(end);
1651
1652 const bool toplevel = !source_parent.isValid();
1653 const bool recursive_accepted = filter_recursive && !toplevel && filterAcceptsRowInternal(source_row: source_parent.row(), source_parent: source_parent.parent());
1654 //Force the creation of a mapping now, even if it's empty.
1655 //We need it because the proxy can be accessed at the moment it emits rowsAboutToBeInserted in insert_source_items
1656 if (!filter_recursive || toplevel || recursive_accepted) {
1657 if (can_create_mapping(source_parent))
1658 create_mapping(source_parent);
1659 if (filter_recursive)
1660 complete_insert = true;
1661 } else {
1662 // The row could have been rejected or the parent might be not yet known... let's try to discover it
1663 QModelIndex top_source_parent = source_parent;
1664 QModelIndex parent = source_parent.parent();
1665 QModelIndex grandParent = parent.parent();
1666
1667 while (parent.isValid() && !filterAcceptsRowInternal(source_row: parent.row(), source_parent: grandParent)) {
1668 top_source_parent = parent;
1669 parent = grandParent;
1670 grandParent = parent.parent();
1671 }
1672
1673 last_top_source = top_source_parent;
1674 }
1675}
1676
1677void QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::_q_sourceRowsInserted(
1678 const QModelIndex &source_parent, int start, int end)
1679{
1680 if (!filter_recursive || complete_insert) {
1681 if (filter_recursive)
1682 complete_insert = false;
1683 source_items_inserted(source_parent, start, end, orient: Qt::Vertical);
1684 if (update_source_sort_column() && dynamic_sortfilter) //previous call to update_source_sort_column may fail if the model has no column.
1685 sort(); // now it should succeed so we need to make sure to sort again
1686 return;
1687 }
1688
1689 if (filter_recursive) {
1690 bool accept = false;
1691
1692 for (int row = start; row <= end; ++row) {
1693 if (filterAcceptsRowInternal(source_row: row, source_parent)) {
1694 accept = true;
1695 break;
1696 }
1697 }
1698
1699 if (!accept) // the new rows have no descendants that match the filter, filter them out.
1700 return;
1701
1702 // last_top_source should now become visible
1703 _q_sourceDataChanged(source_top_left: last_top_source, source_bottom_right: last_top_source, roles: QList<int>());
1704 }
1705}
1706
1707void QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::_q_sourceRowsAboutToBeRemoved(
1708 const QModelIndex &source_parent, int start, int end)
1709{
1710 itemsBeingRemoved = QRowsRemoval(source_parent, start, end);
1711 source_items_about_to_be_removed(source_parent, start, end,
1712 orient: Qt::Vertical);
1713}
1714
1715void QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::_q_sourceRowsRemoved(
1716 const QModelIndex &source_parent, int start, int end)
1717{
1718 itemsBeingRemoved = QRowsRemoval();
1719 source_items_removed(source_parent, start, end, orient: Qt::Vertical);
1720
1721 if (filter_recursive) {
1722 // Find out if removing this visible row means that some ascendant
1723 // row can now be hidden.
1724 // We go up until we find a row that should still be visible
1725 // and then make QSFPM re-evaluate the last one we saw before that, to hide it.
1726
1727 QModelIndex to_hide;
1728 QModelIndex source_ascendant = source_parent;
1729
1730 while (source_ascendant.isValid()) {
1731 if (filterAcceptsRowInternal(source_row: source_ascendant.row(), source_parent: source_ascendant.parent()))
1732 break;
1733
1734 to_hide = source_ascendant;
1735 source_ascendant = source_ascendant.parent();
1736 }
1737
1738 if (to_hide.isValid())
1739 _q_sourceDataChanged(source_top_left: to_hide, source_bottom_right: to_hide, roles: QList<int>());
1740 }
1741}

1785

1787 return; //we sort according to the root column only

1797 }

1848/*!
1849 \since 4.1
1850 \class QSortFilterProxyModel
1851 \inmodule QtCore
1852 \brief The QSortFilterProxyModel class provides support for sorting and
1853 filtering data passed between another model and a view.
1854
1855 \ingroup model-view
1856
1857 QSortFilterProxyModel can be used for sorting items, filtering out items,
1858 or both. The model transforms the structure of a source model by mapping
1859 the model indexes it supplies to new indexes, corresponding to different
1860 locations, for views to use. This approach allows a given source model to
1861 be restructured as far as views are concerned without requiring any
1862 transformations on the underlying data, and without duplicating the data in
1863 memory.
1864
1865 Let's assume that we want to sort and filter the items provided by a custom
1866 model. The code to set up the model and the view, \e without sorting and
1867 filtering, would look like this:
1868
1869 \snippet qsortfilterproxymodel-details/main.cpp 1
1870
1871 To add sorting and filtering support to \c MyItemModel, we need to create
1872 a QSortFilterProxyModel, call setSourceModel() with the \c MyItemModel as
1873 argument, and install the QSortFilterProxyModel on the view:
1874
1875 \snippet qsortfilterproxymodel-details/main.cpp 0
1876 \snippet qsortfilterproxymodel-details/main.cpp 2
1877
1878 At this point, neither sorting nor filtering is enabled; the original data
1879 is displayed in the view. Any changes made through the
1880 QSortFilterProxyModel are applied to the original model.
1881
1882 The QSortFilterProxyModel acts as a wrapper for the original model. If you
1883 need to convert source \l{QModelIndex}es to sorted/filtered model indexes
1884 or vice versa, use mapToSource(), mapFromSource(), mapSelectionToSource(),
1885 and mapSelectionFromSource().
1886
1887 \note By default, the model dynamically re-sorts and re-filters data
1888 whenever the original model changes. This behavior can be changed by
1889 setting the \l{QSortFilterProxyModel::dynamicSortFilter}{dynamicSortFilter}
1890 property.
1891
1892 The \l{itemviews/basicsortfiltermodel}{Basic Sort/Filter Model} and
1893 \l{itemviews/customsortfiltermodel}{Custom Sort/Filter Model} examples
1894 illustrate how to use QSortFilterProxyModel to perform basic sorting and
1895 filtering and how to subclass it to implement custom behavior.
1896
1897 \section1 Sorting
1898
1899 QTableView and QTreeView have a
1900 \l{QTreeView::sortingEnabled}{sortingEnabled} property that controls
1901 whether the user can sort the view by clicking the view's horizontal
1902 header. For example:
1903
1904 \snippet qsortfilterproxymodel-details/main.cpp 3
1905
1906 When this feature is on (the default is off), clicking on a header section
1907 sorts the items according to that column. By clicking repeatedly, the user
1908 can alternate between ascending and descending order.
1909
1910 \image qsortfilterproxymodel-sorting.png A sorted QTreeView
1911
1912 Behind the scene, the view calls the sort() virtual function on the model
1913 to reorder the data in the model. To make your data sortable, you can
1914 either implement sort() in your model, or use a QSortFilterProxyModel to
1915 wrap your model -- QSortFilterProxyModel provides a generic sort()
1916 reimplementation that operates on the sortRole() (Qt::DisplayRole by
1917 default) of the items and that understands several data types, including
1918 \c int, QString, and QDateTime. For hierarchical models, sorting is applied
1919 recursively to all child items. String comparisons are case sensitive by
1920 default; this can be changed by setting the \l{QSortFilterProxyModel::}
1921 {sortCaseSensitivity} property.
1922
1923 Custom sorting behavior is achieved by subclassing
1924 QSortFilterProxyModel and reimplementing lessThan(), which is
1925 used to compare items. For example:
1926
1927 \snippet ../widgets/itemviews/customsortfiltermodel/mysortfilterproxymodel.cpp 5
1928
1929 (This code snippet comes from the
1930 \l{itemviews/customsortfiltermodel}{Custom Sort/Filter Model}
1931 example.)
1932
1933 An alternative approach to sorting is to disable sorting on the view and to
1934 impose a certain order to the user. This is done by explicitly calling
1935 sort() with the desired column and order as arguments on the
1936 QSortFilterProxyModel (or on the original model if it implements sort()).
1937 For example:
1938
1939 \snippet qsortfilterproxymodel-details/main.cpp 4
1940
1941 QSortFilterProxyModel can be sorted by column -1, in which case it returns
1942 to the sort order of the underlying source model.
1943
1944 \section1 Filtering
1945
1946 In addition to sorting, QSortFilterProxyModel can be used to hide items
1947 that do not match a certain filter. The filter is specified using a QRegularExpression
1948 object and is applied to the filterRole() (Qt::DisplayRole by default) of
1949 each item, for a given column. The QRegularExpression object can be used to match a
1950 regular expression, a wildcard pattern, or a fixed string. For example:
1951
1952 \snippet qsortfilterproxymodel-details/main.cpp 5
1953
1954 For hierarchical models, the filter is applied recursively to all children.
1955 If a parent item doesn't match the filter, none of its children will be
1956 shown.
1957
1958 A common use case is to let the user specify the filter regular expression,
1959 wildcard pattern, or fixed string in a QLineEdit and to connect the
1960 \l{QLineEdit::textChanged()}{textChanged()} signal to setFilterRegularExpression(),
1961 setFilterWildcard(), or setFilterFixedString() to reapply the filter.
1962
1963 Custom filtering behavior can be achieved by reimplementing the
1964 filterAcceptsRow() and filterAcceptsColumn() functions. For
1965 example (from the \l{itemviews/customsortfiltermodel}
1966 {Custom Sort/Filter Model} example), the following implementation ignores
1967 the \l{QSortFilterProxyModel::filterKeyColumn}{filterKeyColumn} property
1968 and performs filtering on columns 0, 1, and 2:
1969
1970 \snippet ../widgets/itemviews/customsortfiltermodel/mysortfilterproxymodel.cpp 3
1971
1972 (This code snippet comes from the
1973 \l{itemviews/customsortfiltermodel}{Custom Sort/Filter Model}
1974 example.)
1975
1976 If you are working with large amounts of filtering and have to invoke
1977 invalidateFilter() repeatedly, using beginResetModel() / endResetModel() may
1978 be more efficient, depending on the implementation of your model. However,
1979 beginResetModel() / endResetModel() returns the
1980 proxy model to its original state, losing selection information, and will
1981 cause the proxy model to be repopulated.
1982
1983 \section1 Subclassing
1984
1985 Since QAbstractProxyModel and its subclasses are derived from
1986 QAbstractItemModel, much of the same advice about subclassing normal models
1987 also applies to proxy models. In addition, it is worth noting that many of
1988 the default implementations of functions in this class are written so that
1989 they call the equivalent functions in the relevant source model. This
1990 simple proxying mechanism may need to be overridden for source models with
1991 more complex behavior; for example, if the source model provides a custom
1992 hasChildren() implementation, you should also provide one in the proxy
1993 model.
1994
1995 \note Some general guidelines for subclassing models are available in the
1996 \l{Model Subclassing Reference}.
1997
1998 \sa QAbstractProxyModel, QAbstractItemModel, {Model/View Programming},
1999 {Basic Sort/Filter Model Example}, {Custom Sort/Filter Model Example}, QIdentityProxyModel
2000*/
2001

2390/*!
2391 \reimp
2392*/
2393bool QSortFilterProxyModel::removeRows(int row, int count, const QModelIndex &parent)
2394{
2395 Q_D(QSortFilterProxyModel);
2396 if (row < 0 || count <= 0)
2397 return false;
2398 QModelIndex source_parent = mapToSource(proxyIndex: parent);
2399 if (parent.isValid() && !source_parent.isValid())
2400 return false;
2401 QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::Mapping *m = d->create_mapping(source_parent).value();
2402 if (row + count > m->source_rows.size())
2403 return false;
2404 if ((count == 1)
2405 || ((d->source_sort_column < 0) && (m->proxy_rows.size() == m->source_rows.size()))) {
2406 int source_row = m->source_rows.at(i: row);
2407 return d->model->removeRows(row: source_row, count, parent: source_parent);
2408 }
2409 // remove corresponding source intervals
2410 // ### if this proves to be slow, we can switch to single-row removal
2411 QList<int> rows;
2412 rows.reserve(size: count);
2413 for (int i = row; i < row + count; ++i)
2414 rows.append(t: m->source_rows.at(i));
2415 std::sort(first: rows.begin(), last: rows.end());
2416
2417 int pos = rows.size() - 1;
2418 bool ok = true;
2419 while (pos >= 0) {
2420 const int source_end = rows.at(i: pos--);
2421 int source_start = source_end;
2422 while ((pos >= 0) && (rows.at(i: pos) == (source_start - 1))) {
2423 --source_start;
2424 --pos;
2425 }
2426 ok = ok && d->model->removeRows(row: source_start, count: source_end - source_start + 1,
2427 parent: source_parent);
2428 }
2429 return ok;
2430}

2588/*!
2589 \since 5.12
2590 \property QSortFilterProxyModel::filterRegularExpression
2591 \brief the QRegularExpression used to filter the contents of the source model
2592
2593 Setting this property through the QRegularExpression overload overwrites the
2594 current \l{QSortFilterProxyModel::filterCaseSensitivity}{filterCaseSensitivity}.
2595 By default, the QRegularExpression is an empty string matching all contents.
2596
2597 If no QRegularExpression or an empty string is set, everything in the source
2598 model will be accepted.
2599
2600 \note Setting this property propagates the case sensitivity of the new
2601 regular expression to the \l filterCaseSensitivity property, and so breaks
2602 its binding. Likewise explicitly setting \l filterCaseSensitivity changes
2603 the case sensitivity of the current regular expression, thereby breaking
2604 its binding.
2605
2606 \sa filterCaseSensitivity, setFilterWildcard(), setFilterFixedString()
2607*/

2614QBindable<QRegularExpression> QSortFilterProxyModel::bindableFilterRegularExpression()
2615{
2616 Q_D(QSortFilterProxyModel);
2617 return QBindable<QRegularExpression>(&d->filter_regularexpression);
2618}
2619
2620void QSortFilterProxyModel::setFilterRegularExpression(const QRegularExpression &regularExpression)
2621{
2622 Q_D(QSortFilterProxyModel);
2623 Qt::beginPropertyUpdateGroup();
2624 const bool regExpChanged = regularExpression != d->filter_regularexpression.value();
2625 d->filter_regularexpression.removeBindingUnlessInWrapper();
2626 d->filter_casesensitive.removeBindingUnlessInWrapper();
2627 const Qt::CaseSensitivity cs = filterCaseSensitivity();
2628 d->filter_about_to_be_changed();
2629 const Qt::CaseSensitivity updatedCs =
2630 regularExpression.patternOptions() & QRegularExpression::CaseInsensitiveOption
2631 ? Qt::CaseInsensitive : Qt::CaseSensitive;
2632 d->filter_regularexpression.setValueBypassingBindings(regularExpression);
2633 if (cs != updatedCs)
2634 d->filter_casesensitive.setValueBypassingBindings(updatedCs);
2635 d->filter_changed(dir: QSortFilterProxyModelPrivate::Direction::Rows);
2636 // Do not change the evaluation logic, but notify only if the regular
2637 // expression has actually changed.
2638 if (regExpChanged)
2639 d->filter_regularexpression.notify();
2640 if (cs != updatedCs)
2641 d->filter_casesensitive.notify();
2642 Qt::endPropertyUpdateGroup();
2643}

2895/*!
2896 \since 4.2
2897 \property QSortFilterProxyModel::dynamicSortFilter
2898 \brief whether the proxy model is dynamically sorted and filtered
2899 whenever the contents of the source model change
2900
2901 Note that you should not update the source model through the proxy
2902 model when dynamicSortFilter is true. For instance, if you set the
2903 proxy model on a QComboBox, then using functions that update the
2904 model, e.g., \l{QComboBox::}{addItem()}, will not work as
2905 expected. An alternative is to set dynamicSortFilter to false and
2906 call \l{QSortFilterProxyModel::}{sort()} after adding items to the
2907 QComboBox.
2908
2909 The default value is true.
2910
2911 \sa sortColumn()
2912*/
2913bool QSortFilterProxyModel::dynamicSortFilter() const
2914{
2915 Q_D(const QSortFilterProxyModel);
2916 return d->dynamic_sortfilter;
2917}
2918
2919void QSortFilterProxyModel::setDynamicSortFilter(bool enable)
2920{
2921 // While introducing new bindable properties, we still update the value
2922 // unconditionally (even if it didn't really change), and call the
2923 // sort() method, so that we do not break any code.
2924 // However we do notify the observing bindings only if the value has
2925 // actually changed.
2926 Q_D(QSortFilterProxyModel);

3191 the following QVariant types:
3192
3193 \list
3194 \li QMetaType::Int
3195 \li QMetaType::UInt
3196 \li QMetaType::LongLong
3197 \li QMetaType::ULongLong

3203 \li QMetaType::QDateTime
3204 \li QMetaType::QString

3232 and \a source_parent should be included in the model; otherwise returns
3233 false.
3234

3236 matches the filter string, wildcard string or regular expression.
3237

3248 if (d->filter_regularexpression.value().pattern().isEmpty())
3249 return true;

3252 if (d->filter_column == -1) {

3254 QModelIndex source_index = d->model->index(row: source_row, column, parent: source_parent);
3255 QString key = d->model->data(index: source_index, role: d->filter_role).toString();
3256 if (key.contains(re: d->filter_regularexpression.value()))
3257 return true;
3258 }
3259 return false;

3261
3262 if (d->filter_column >= column_count) // the column may not exist
3263 return true;
3264 QModelIndex source_index = d->model->index(row: source_row, column: d->filter_column, parent: source_parent);
3265 QString key = d->model->data(index: source_index, role: d->filter_role).toString();
